<br>
The standard spell effects list window works fine if you set it to 100% transparency, and park it along the top of your screen. You will still see your effects icons, but with no distracting window border. It's pretty much like way effects were listed in the original -original- UI; except in the first UI they made too much clutter, whereas nowadays they don't.<br>
<br>
So if you haven't tried it like that, try it!<br>
